      },
      "source": [
        "## Elementary While Loop"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NQ4fQVUJKWol"
      },
      "source": [
        "```\n",
        "while condition:  # evaluate condition to find its value; if it is False, stop the loop\n",
        "   loop-body      # if the value of condition is true, do this and go to the beginning of loop and do the same again\n",
        "# Once the loop is stopped, execute the code in this line.\n",
        "```\n",
        "First, `condition` is evaulated.  If it is true, `loop-body` is executed and loops back to evaluated `condition` again. Once, `condition` is false, the repetition stops and the statement after `loop-body` is executed.  The `loop-body` is a block of code which is a number of consecutive code lines with the same indentation.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "The following example shows a simple while that prints 1 to 10. "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6hHMH6arg2fq",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "e467e0cd-c21a-4f63-f9d6-ce923061be46"
      },
      "source": [
        "i = 1\n",
        "while i<=10:\n",
        "    print(i)\n",
        "    i = i+1\n",
        "print('----')"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
