    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FRnlFgCtggix"
      },
      "source": [
        "The following program determines if a positive number is a prime or a composite. When the input is not 1, the while loop in this program tests if `i` divides `n`. The loop terminates either when we find `i` that divides `n` or we try all `i`=2,3,..., `n`-1. \n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "*   If the loop terminates when i==n, it means we try all `i`=2,3,..., `n`-1 and none of them divides `n`.  In this case, `n` is a prime.\n",
        "*   If the loop terminates when `n%i` is 0, it means we find an integer `i` that divides `n`.  In this case, `n` is not a prime."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "hjmgSa7aFPak"
      },
      "source": [
        "n = int(input('enter a positive integer:'))\n",
        "if n==1:\n",
        "    print('1 is a composite.')\n",
        "else\n",
        "    i = 2\n",
        "    while n%i!=0 and i<n:\n",
        "        i = i+1\n",
        "    if i==n:\n",
        "        print(n, 'is a prime.')\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(n, 'is a composite.')"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MxkB0Z-Br5tm"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Break"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2WIQU9ChcjdS"
      },
      "source": [
        "```\n",
        "while condition0:  # line 1\n",
        "   ...             # line 2\n",
        "   if condition1:  # line 3\n",
        "      break        # line 4\n",
        "   ...             # line 5\n",
        "...                # line 6\n",
        "```\n",
        "`break` makes a loop terminate (go to line 6). \n",
        "\n",
        "In a loop, `break` is normally used in an if statement. In the following example, we use `break` to to terminate the loop when a factor of `n` is found."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "97OcqEiWpGe-"
      },
      "source": [
        "In the following program, `break` is used to terminate the loop when a factor of `n` is found."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GVGQoNRacqi6"
      },
      "source": [
        "n = int(input('enter a positive integer:'))\n",
        "if n==1:\n",
        "    print('1 is a composite.')\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    i = 2\n",
        "    while i<n:\n",
        "        if n%i==0:\n",
        "            break\n",
        "        i=i+1\n",
        "    if i==n:\n",
        "        print(n, 'is a prime.')\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(n, 'is a composite.')"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vobupWiUkLdr"
      },
      "source": [
        "If `break` is placed in a nested loop (which we will see a bit later), it makes the innermost loop that contains  `break` terminates."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_J1_7Gtkr-ZZ"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Continue"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ulA4uMqkkxQV"
      },
      "source": [
        "```\n",
        "while condition0:  # line 1\n",
        "   ...             # line 2\n",
        "   if condition1:  # line 3\n",
        "      continue     # line 4\n",
        "   ...             # line 5\n",
        "...                # line 6\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "`continue` makes the execution skip the rest of the loop body (line 5) in that iteration and start the execution of the next iteration of the loop (line 1).\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "   "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "F1K5tUrckwX-"
      },
      "source": [
        "total = 0\n",
        "i = 1\n",
        "while i<=7:\n",
        "    exp = float(input('Day '+str(i)+' expense:'))\n",
        "    if exp<0:\n",
        "        print('Expense cannot be negative')\n",
        "        continue\n",
        "    total = total+exp\n",
        "    i = i+1\n",
        "print('Weekly expense =',total)    "
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YJ46A5wDsuS6"
      },
      "source": [
        "If `continue` is placed in a nested loop, it skips the rest of the loop body of the innermost loop that contains that `continue`."
      ]
    },
