      "source": [
        "## While-else"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "eUgOA5FynaCd"
      },
      "source": [
        "An else clause can be used with while loop. (The indentation of `while` and `else` must be the same.)  The block of code in `else` clause is executed if the loop terminates normally, i.e. does not terminates with `break`.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "while A:\n",
        "   B\n",
        "else:\n",
        "   C\n",
        "```\n",
        "works like\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "while A:\n",
        "   B\n",
        "if A:\n",
        "   pass # which means do nothing\n",
        "else:\n",
        "   C\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "DhxSiuDsvXbA"
      },
      "source": [
        "The following example uses the else clause for the code that must be executed when the loop terminates normally."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GdiQc2OKnoIi"
      },
      "source": [
        "n = int(input('enter a positive integer:'))\n",
        "if n==1:\n",
        "    print('1 is a composite.')\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    i = 2\n",
        "    while i<n:\n",
        "        if n%i==0:\n",
        "            print(n,'is a composite.')\n",
        "            break\n",
        "        i=i+1\n",
        "#   if i<n:  pass    \n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(n,'is a prime.')"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pRj7G5uMq_FQ"
      },
      "source": [
        "`else` clause can also be used with `for` loop which will be discussed later."
      ]
