      "source": [
        "The following example which is a program that finds prime factors is an example of nested loops.  The outside loop runs for `i`=2,3,4,... to test if `i` is a factor of `n`. The inner loop divides `n` by `i` until `i` does not divide `n` in order to get only prime factors."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Bo3adoplKUxj"
      },
      "source": [
        "n = int(input('Enter a positive integer:'))\n",
        "i = 2\n",
        "print('Prime factor of',n,':')\n",
        "while n>1:  # n=12\n",
        "    c = 0   # i=2\n",
        "    while n%i==0: \n",
        "        n = n/i  # n = 3\n",
        "        c = c+1\n",
        "    if c>0: print(i)\n",
        "    i = i+1"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tviAQ5t-roq3"
      },
      "source": [
        "If `break` is placed in a nested loop (which we will see a bit later), it makes the innermost loop that contains  `break` terminates."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "TaqPHAc06UwK"
