      "source": [
        "## For-in-range"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ZGnli4Db_aM5"
      },
      "source": [
        "`range` is a function that generates a collection of integers one by one. \n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "*   `range(c)` generates `0, 1, 2, ..., c-1`\n",
        "*   `range(b, e)` generates `b, b+1, b+2,..., e-1`\n",
        "*  ` range(b, e, s)` generates `b, b+s, b+2s,..., b+ks`, where `b+ks` is the largest integer that is less than `e`. \n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "`range` is often used together with `for` to iterate on a collection of integers.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "iqSGdodZB0k-"
